==English==

===Etymology===
Latin < Ancient Greek ''[[apsinthion]]''< ''[[apsinthos]]''. The Ancient Greek word is of uncertain origin. May be from Persian ''[[aspand]]'', ''[[spand]]'' ("wormwood"). (See also [[w:Absinthe#Etymology]].)

===Noun===
#''(Botany):'' The common [[wormwood]] (''[[Artemisia]] absinthium''), an [[intensely]] bitter plant, used as a [[tonic]] and for making the oil of wormwood.
